inverse.description: Use as component background in high-contrast situations.

placeholder.description: Use for placeholder text in fields

inverse.description: Use for primary text on an inverse layer

inverse-secondary.description: Use for secondary text on an inverse layer.

error.description: Use for error text/icons outside of a notice.

success.description: Use for success text/icons outside of a notice.

background.description: The background color for the top toolbar

default.description: Default text color for the top toolbar's contents

primary.description: Use for monotype output in an invere layer.

secondary.description: Use for timestamp or secondary monotype output in an inverse layer.

background.description: Use for the pseudo terminal window background color.

rem.description: Use as the base rem value for calculations in Figma Tokens. In production all size values should be in rems, which is modifiable by the user. Since Figma Tokens doesn't support different units, we use this variable to do rem calculations. For our purposes, we're setting the rem value to 16px.

1.description: these are non-responsive font sizes used for body copy, helper text and other elements that don't need to respond to viewport width.

s.description: All of these fontSizes.figma tokens are used exclusively for convenience in Figma. We use them to generate the suite of styles we use in Figma and correspond to the screen size values in breakpoints. They are a representation of the responsive sizes generated by the clamp functions in the fontSizes.responsive object

1.description: These are the formulas that generate the responsive type sizes in production. Calculations like this aren't supported in Figma so we use the manually calculated fontSizes.figma tokens to generate a suite of styles that approximate the font size at our standard breakpoints.

3.description: Use for small and medium sized headings.

5.description: Use for body-sized text in long-form reading applications.

description.value: In production, all units are in %.

responsive.description: This is the responsive line height for the responsive type sizes.

none.description: in Figma, letter spacing values need to be % but in production they need to be expressed in em to work with varable fonts
